name: Slow-Cooked Eggplant with Lemon and Fennel Seeds

steps.instruction: Place a rack in middle of oven and preheat to 350°

Cut the eggplants in half
Toss eggplant, garlic, lemon zest, oil, fennel seeds, and salt in a shallow 2-qt. baking dish to combine
Turn garlic cut side down, then roast eggplant, tossing 2 or 3 times, until golden brown, very tender, and crisp around edges and on cut sides, 70–80 minutes
Let cool slightly, then add lemon juice and toss to coat
